Start Using EJS (Embedded JS) :

	1. Create a new folder called "4.0 EJS".
	2. Initialize NPM and install Express and ejs

		i. npm init -y
	       ii. npm i express ejs
	      
	3. Create the following files and folders : 

		i. mkdir views; touch index.js views/index.ejs

	4. Use the JS getDay() method to build a website that gives advice based on the day of the week.



Different EJS Tags :

	1. <%= variable %>               : JS output (value of the variable)
	2. <% console.log("Hello") %>    : JS Execute (only execution but not showing the output)
	3. <%- <h1>Hello</h1> %>         : Render HTML (shows the html structure of the code which is under the starting and closing tag)
	4. <%% %%>                       : excape EJS tag (show <% or %>)
	5. <%# This is a comment %>      : stop execution (commen out something)
	6. <%- include("<FILE NAME")%>   : insert another file
		Example :
		<%- include("header.ejs")%>   : insert another EJS file

